Yes, you can convert a given string to lowercase in Objective-C using the `lowercaseString` method of the `NSString` class. Here's a simple example:

```objective-c
NSString *originalString = @"Hello, World!";
NSString *lowercaseString = [originalString lowercaseString];

NSLog(@"Original String: %@", originalString);
NSLog(@"Lowercase String: %@", lowercaseString);
```

In this example, `lowercaseString` will contain `"hello, world!"`. The `lowercaseString` method returns a new string with all the characters in lowercase.
